📌 2️⃣ Sequence Diagram (Detailed)

This sequence diagram represents the flow of a POST request from the client to CosmosDB.

@startuml
actor Client
participant "Filter" as F
participant "Controller" as C
participant "Service" as S
participant "Repository" as R
database "CosmosDB" as DB
participant "Exception Handler" as EH
participant "Logger" as L

Client -> C: Sends POST Request
C -> F: Extract Request ID (If Used)
F -> L: Log Request Metadata
F -> C: Pass Request to Controller

C -> S: Call Service Layer with DTO
S -> R: Convert DTO to Model & Call Repository
R -> DB: Execute Query in CosmosDB

alt Database Query Success
    DB --> R: Returns Data
    R --> S: Returns Success Response
    S --> C: Returns 201 Created
    C --> Client: Responds with 201 Created
else Database Query Fails
    DB --> R: Throws Exception
    R --> EH: Global Exception Handler Catches Error
    EH --> Client: Responds with 500 Internal Server Error
end

L -> L: Log API Response
@enduml

📌 How to Import into Visio
	1.	Copy the sequence diagram code above.
	2.	Paste it into PlantUML Online Editor or a tool like IntelliJ / VS Code.
	3.	Export as SVG and import into Visio.

⸻

📌 Summary: What’s Included in Both Diagrams?

Component	Flowchart	Sequence Diagram	Description
Client (User/API Call)	✅	✅	Sends the API request
Filter (If Used)	✅	✅	Extracts metadata (Request ID)
Controller	✅	✅	Receives and validates the request
Service Layer	✅	✅	Processes business logic
Repository Layer	✅	✅	Executes DB query
Database (CosmosDB)	✅	✅	Stores data
Exception Handling	✅	✅	Catches 400/500 errors
Logging (Logback.xml)	✅	✅	Logs requests, responses, errors



